---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="ZERO OS — The Regime Problem" description="Why chaos mathematics changes everything about trading signals. Hurst exponent, DFA, and Lyapunov — the three indicators that tell you whether your other indicators are lying.">

<div class="page">
<div class="page-inner">

  <!-- NAV -->
  <nav class="thesis-nav">
    <a href="/" class="nav-back"><span class="p">←</span> ZERO OS</a>
    <span class="nav-label dim">/thesis</span>
  </nav>

  <!-- HERO PANE -->
  <div class="pane pane-hero">
    <div class="pane-header"><span class="p">■</span> THESIS</div>
    <div class="pane-body">
      <h1 class="thesis-title">The Regime Problem</h1>
      <p class="thesis-subtitle">Why every indicator you use assumes one market. There are many.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CONTENT: TWO-COLUMN -->
  <div class="pane-grid">

    <!-- LEFT: The argument -->
    <div class="pane">
      <div class="pane-header"><span class="a">■</span> THE ASSUMPTION</div>
      <div class="pane-body">
        <p>Every technical indicator in crypto — RSI, MACD, Bollinger Bands, moving average crossovers — contains the same hidden assumption:</p>
        <p class="highlight">The market behaves the same way tomorrow as it did yesterday.</p>
        <p>This is false. Markets switch between distinct states: trending, mean-reverting, chaotic, and transitional. An RSI signal that works beautifully in a trending state becomes noise in a mean-reverting one. A mean-reversion strategy that prints money in calm markets gets destroyed when a trend emerges.</p>
        <p>The question isn't <em>"what does the indicator say?"</em></p>
        <p class="highlight">It's "does this indicator even apply right now?"</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- RIGHT: The punchline -->
    <div class="pane">
      <div class="pane-header"><span class="p">■</span> THE PUNCHLINE</div>
      <div class="pane-body">
        <p class="highlight">A MACD crossover in a trending state is meaningful. The same crossover in a mean-reverting state is a trap.</p>
        <p>Traditional platforms show you the crossover. We show you the state first. Then you decide if the crossover matters.</p>
        <p>This is the difference between an indicator dashboard and a trading intelligence system.</p>
        <div class="edge-contrast">
          <div class="edge-row">
            <span class="edge-them dim">Indicator dashboard: RSI = 72 → overbought</span>
            <span class="edge-us p">→ Intelligence: RSI = 72 in a trending state → momentum, not exhaustion</span>
          </div>
          <div class="edge-row">
            <span class="edge-them dim">Indicator dashboard: MACD crossover → buy signal</span>
            <span class="edge-us p">→ Intelligence: MACD crossover in chaos → noise, ignore it</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- THREE INDICATORS -->
  <div class="pane-full">
    <div class="pane">
      <div class="pane-header"><span class="ice">■</span> THREE CHAOS INDICATORS</div>
      <div class="pane-body">
        <div class="indicator-grid">
          <div class="indicator-card">
            <h3 class="indicator-name p">Hurst Exponent (H)</h3>
            <p class="indicator-desc">Measures long-term memory in a time series.</p>
            <div class="indicator-values">
              <span class="iv"><span class="p">H &lt; 0.5</span> = mean-reverting (prices snap back)</span>
              <span class="iv"><span class="a">H &gt; 0.5</span> = trending (momentum is real)</span>
              <span class="iv"><span class="dim">H ≈ 0.5</span> = random walk (signals are meaningless)</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="indicator-card">
            <h3 class="indicator-name p">Detrended Fluctuation Analysis (DFA)</h3>
            <p class="indicator-desc">A more robust version of Hurst that handles non-stationary data. When Hurst and DFA agree, you have a strong signal. When they diverge, the market is in transition — the most dangerous zone.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="indicator-card">
            <h3 class="indicator-name p">Lyapunov Exponent (λ)</h3>
            <p class="indicator-desc">Measures sensitivity to initial conditions — literally, chaos level. High λ means tiny input changes cause wildly different outcomes.</p>
            <p class="indicator-highlight">High Lyapunov = reduce position size. The market is unpredictable even with perfect information.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- REFERENCES + CTA -->
  <div class="pane-grid">
    <div class="pane">
      <div class="pane-header"><span class="dim">■</span> REFERENCES</div>
      <div class="pane-body">
        <ul class="ref-list">
          <li>Mandelbrot, B. (1963). "The Variation of Certain Speculative Prices." <em>Journal of Business</em></li>
          <li>Hurst, H.E. (1951). "Long-term Storage Capacity of Reservoirs." <em>Trans. ASCE</em></li>
          <li>Peng, C.-K. et al. (1994). "Mosaic organization of DNA nucleotide sequences." <em>Physical Review E</em> — original DFA paper</li>
          <li>Rosenstein, M.T. et al. (1993). "A practical method for calculating largest Lyapunov exponents." <em>Physica D</em></li>
          <li>Di Matteo, T. et al. (2005). "Long-term memories of developed and emerging markets." <em>J. Banking & Finance</em></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="pane pane-access">
      <div class="pane-header"><span class="p">■</span> ACCESS</div>
      <div class="pane-body" style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;justify-content:center;gap:1rem;">
        <p class="access-line">The intelligence layer is built.</p>
        <p class="access-line">Signal API is pre-launch.</p>
        <p class="access-line dim">Design partners get first access.</p>
        <a href="/#access" class="btn-primary">Request Early Access →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- FOOTER -->
  <footer class="thesis-footer">
    <span class="p">◇</span> <span class="dim">ZERO OS</span>
  </footer>

</div>
</div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page {
    margin: 0.5rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(200,255,0,0.4);
    min-height: calc(100vh - 1rem);
    padding: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .page-inner {
    max-width: 1400px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0.75rem 2rem 2rem;
  }

  /* NAV */
  .thesis-nav {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 0.75rem 0 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .nav-back {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }
  .nav-back:hover { color: var(--phosphor); }
  .nav-label {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  }

  /* PANE SYSTEM (matches homepage) */
  .pane-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .pane-full { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .pane {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.4);
  }
  .pane-header {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: rgba(10,10,10,0.6);
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }
  .pane-body {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .pane-hero { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

  /* TYPOGRAPHY */
  .thesis-title {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 5vw, 2.8rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .thesis-subtitle {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .highlight {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  /* INDICATORS */
  .indicator-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .indicator-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 1rem;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
  }
  .indicator-name {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .indicator-desc {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .indicator-values {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.3rem;
  }
  .iv {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }
  .indicator-highlight {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  /* EDGE CONTRAST */
  .edge-contrast { margin-top: 1rem; }
  .edge-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.15rem;
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(26,26,26,0.3);
  }
  .edge-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .edge-them {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-decoration: line-through;
    opacity: 0.5;
  }
  .edge-us {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* REFERENCES */
  .ref-list {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.8;
    padding-left: 1rem;
  }
  .ref-list li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }

  /* ACCESS */
  .access-line {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .btn-primary {
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--phosphor);
    background: transparent;
    border: 1px solid var(--phosphor);
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    text-align: center;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 0.3s, box-shadow 0.3s;
  }
  .btn-primary:hover {
    background: rgba(200,255,0,0.08);
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(200,255,0,0.1);
  }

  /* FOOTER */
  .thesis-footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1.5rem 0;
    font-family: var(--font-head);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
  }

  /* MOBILE */
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .pane-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .indicator-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .page-inner { padding: 0.5rem 1rem 1.25rem; }
  }
</style>
